.NAME
       zappy_ai - client to drive an inhabitant through orders sent to the server

.SYNOPSIS
       zappy_ai [OPTIONS]

.DESCRIPTION
       zappy_ai is a client used to control an inhabitant in the world generated by the zappy_server. It sends orders to the server to interact with the world.

.OPTIONS
       -p, --port PORT
              Specifies the port number to connect to.

       -n, --name TEAM_NAME
              Specifies the name of the team.

       -h, --host HOST
              Specifies the hostname of the machine to connect to. Defaults to localhost if not specified.

.USAGE
       Example usage:

              ./zappy_ai -p 4242 -n team1 -h localhost

